overview: The user initiated a request for a comprehensive review of their sleep
  questionnaire application, which included database and API endpoints, against
  a detailed specification and Statement of Work. The primary goal was to ensure
  all acceptance criteria were met and to identify any missing functionalities.
  The assistant conducted a thorough code review to understand the current
  implementation and then formulated a detailed plan outlining the identified
  gaps and missing features, prioritizing them based on criticality.
  Subsequently, the assistant proceeded to implement the high-priority items
  from the plan. This involved integrating a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness,
  complete with critical safety messaging for high scores. Detection and
  reporting mechanisms for Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome were also added. Furthermore, a new "Resources &
  Next Steps" section was incorporated into both the web and PDF reports,
  providing placeholder outbound links to various sleep specialists, behavioral
  sleep medicine providers, mental health resources, and educational materials.
  The implementation required modifications across type definitions, validation
  schemas, UI components, and report generation logic.
